nhibition of accretion\nsignificantly reduces the average X-ray luminosity expected for any neutron\nstar wind-fed binary. The present model calculations suggest that long spin\nperiods and stronger magnetic fields are favoured in order to reproduce the\npeculiar behavior of supergiant fast X-ray transients in the X-ray domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Mar 2016 17:37:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Mar 2016 21:35:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-20"}
